<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-08-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="524" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d524">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Newel</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">The
                                        Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-08-05"><hi rend="italic">August 5,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 777.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state that I am
                            informed that Mexico and Venezuela have paid their quotas of the
                            honoraria to the members of the arbitral tribunal constituted in virtue
                            of the protocols of Washington of May 7, 1903.</p>
                        <p>It is expected that the Spanish quota will be paid in a few days.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stanford Newel.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>